research_municipality_step.notes: The City of Groves operates under a mayor-council form of government, with a mayor and four council members elected at-large, and a city manager appointed by the council. Information for Ward 2 is based on November 2024 election results. The official city website lists Rae Shauna Gay as Mayor Pro Tem and Ward 4 Council Member. While the website also lists Rhonda Dugas for Ward 4, the city's structure indicates not more than one council member can be a resident of the same ward, suggesting Rae Shauna Gay is the current representative for Ward 4 given her additional role as Mayor Pro Tem.
